<br>
my average hit without defensive was 600, thats 250(DB) + 10.77*32.5(DI)<br>
<br>
With Defensive up one would expect 250 + 10.77 * 32.5/2 = 425<br>
<br>
So yeah your numbers look right, This was quite possibly simply due to random variations between my 2 limited logs with Evasive and Defensive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umikar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/19/02 11:31:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uber Tanking with CA: Evasive vs Defensive</span><hr size=1> Just need a few logs vs the mob with Evasive/Defensive *with misses on* (/eye Chatja) to establish empirically<br>
<br>
- tohit% (for evasive and normally respectively)<br>
- DI/DB<br>
- the distribution of X<br>
- single/double/tripple/quad/(flurry) percentages<br>
<br>
and you can reasonably simulate each disc for comparison. I suggest counting how often you would die after Y rounds of combat given your HP as a good output from your simulation as thats what its all about - not being dead when the CH lands. I personally found such simulations quite interesting.<br>
<br>
Just for kicks I ran a simulation of the emperor with the following parameters (none of which are very well established).<br>
<br>
- tohit% = 58/42<br>
- DI/DB = 250, 32.7<br>
- dist(X) = (10, 4..4, 18)    for X=(1, 2..19, 20)<br>
- s/d/t/q = 15,15,35,35<br>
- HP of tank = 7300<br>
<br>
Defensive: (10,000,000 samples)<br>
4 rounds - 12 (aka meaningless)<br>
5 rounds - 3708<br>
6 rounds - 65881<br>
<br>
So, if you CH once per 5 rounds *exactly* and have say 50 rounds per min you get a mortality risk of 1.1% during the disc. If you heal once every 4 rounds exactly the risk goes to 0 basically.<br>
<br>
Evasive: (10,000,000 samples)<br>
4 rounds - 262<br>
5 rounds - 11093<br>
6 rounds - 89394<br>
<br>
CH every 5 rounds - 50 rounds per min - mortality risk in 3 mins is 3.4%.<br>
<br>
No-disc: (10,000,000 samples)<br>
3 rounds - 5373<br>
4 rounds - 149902<br>
5 rounds - 768750<br>
<br>
Take the numbers for what they are worth - I know lots of assumptions are used here. Kick, Bash, Curse etc are not accounted for for example and the parameters are far from adequately established. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264>Mikar of the Nexus</a><br>High Priest of Brell<br><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net/>The Companions</a><br>The Tribunal 

