<br>
It was my understanding that procs occurred only on damaging hits, and that the way NPC AC and PC ATK worked allowed for the damage the NPC mitigates on a hit (that the NPC receives) to be 0, such that a proc still may occur.  In a reversed situation, the NPC will never have the damage he does mitigated to 0 (Which is why those damn orc centurions in gfay can still hit me for 1, and very rarely hit for like 12) if he hits, due to the differences in the way NPC ATK (or maybe PC AC?) works versus PC ATK (or NPC AC).  I think.<br>
<br>
If what I've stated so far is true (And my poor memory tells me it is, yet I regard it to be a beast most loathsome in its depths of deceit and treachery), then it would stand to reason that taking into account the procs of a mob would influence the choice of a damage reducing discipline before trying to figure in a ratio of DI/DB, especially if such a proc were an AE.  IE if the mob cannot hit you at all, you've effectively removed a (possibly vital) component of the arsenal of the horrid maleficant.<br>
<br>
I suppose what people would want is records in the differences of effectiveness between evasive without any skill in combat agility, and with it at all 3 levels.  A constant AC across the board would help as well, as well as maybe...   Constant Agility as well?  Sorry, I'm unsure as to the number of variables involved in disciplines, I am ignorant  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I'm probably all wrong about how procs work too.  Oh well...<br>
<br>
Incidentally, does anyone know if improved damage focus effect works on procs?  That would be nice. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uzavyynmatrisyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zavyyn Matrisyan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/22/02 7:22:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/28/02 10:37:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uber Tanking with CA: Evasive vs Defensive</span><hr size=1> it seems that npc's can proc weapons with a proc on misses, but innate procs (like VS tap) can only go off when they connect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=1650.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=1650.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=1650.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboa